      "id": "scenario_2a3_s3",
      "name": "Controlled Electrical Shutdown",
      "description": "The motor-pump is running with flow to the outlet. Shut it down in the correct order: open SW_Iso first — this stops the motor, which stops the shaft, which stops the pump. Only then close V_Discharge. Finally de-energise PS1. Closing the discharge valve while the shaft is still turning will dead-head the pump.",
